1
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,180
[Episode 17]

2
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,775
Luckily, Mr. Zhu put in a good word
with your principal,

3
00:01:58,775 --> 00:02:02,737
saying you're a promising student.

4
00:02:02,737 --> 00:02:04,480
Otherwise, your re-enrollment paperwork

5
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,720
would have taken forever.

6
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:10,000
Once I'm back at school,

7
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,560
can you handle things at home on your own?

8
00:02:13,817 --> 00:02:15,240
Of course I can.

9
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,722
Never underestimate your mom.

10
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:21,758
Pocky once read my palm

11
00:02:21,758 --> 00:02:24,710
and said my luck is about to turn.

12
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:27,750
Benefactors and career success
are coming my way.

13
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,040
Him? He also told me

14
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:32,080
I'd become a scientist someday.

15
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,160
Totally out of left field.

16
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,400
I think he was quite accurate.

17
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,430
Don't worry.

18
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:42,120
Ye has already paved the way for us.

19
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,880
Besides, with Xuan Island reopening,

20
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,910
things will be better than before.

21
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:47,440
Supporting the whole family?

22
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,120
Definitely no problem.

23
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,800
You really think so?

24
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,360
Yes, really.

25
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,779
What are you worried about?

26
00:02:55,779 --> 00:02:58,000
Look,
Grandma gets around fine with her wheelchair.

27
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,120
Liu Nian is helping me in the shop.

28
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:02,960
If anything else comes up,
Xi Xi and the others are there.

29
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,388
What's there to worry about?

30
00:03:05,388 --> 00:03:08,578
When I say I can hold things up, I mean it.

31
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,080
You've got this.

32
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:13,641
Right, I've got this.

33
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,896
Mom.

34
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,368
It's a full moon tonight.

35
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,380
Can I come in?

36
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,520
Sure.

37
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:16,360
I got a herbal soak packet from Dr. Zhuang.

38
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,248
Soak your feet for 30 minutes.
It'll make your legs feel better.

39
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:22,370
Got a haircut.

40
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:25,355
Now you look more like a student.

41
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:31,216
- Come on. The water's just right.
- Okay.

42
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,000
It feels so good.

43
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,795
It's like my meridians have been unblocked.

44
00:04:50,043 --> 00:04:51,720
What are you laughing at?

45
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,976
You think it feels like

46
00:04:52,976 --> 00:04:55,007
braised pork trotters, too, don't you?

47
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,226
Exactly.

48
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,218
Mainly because

49
00:05:01,218 --> 00:05:02,505
it smells just like it.

50
00:05:02,505 --> 00:05:03,632
Come to think of it,

51
00:05:03,632 --> 00:05:05,920
this packet does contain Sichuan pepper
and cassia twig.

52
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:09,030
Is Dr. Zhuang really treating my feet
like pork trotters to be braised?

53
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:10,620
He's not that absent-minded.

54
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:13,040
Sichuan pepper and cassia twig
promote blood circulation

55
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,228
and relieve muscle tension.

56
00:05:20,436 --> 00:05:23,190
I really owe you one today.

57
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:24,440
Otherwise,

58
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:26,640
I don't know how I would've made it back

59
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,566
after those twenty laps.

60
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:31,929
Honestly,

61
00:05:31,929 --> 00:05:33,160
you didn't have to.

62
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,840
Yes, I did.

63
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,902
A bet is a bet.

64
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:39,040
It's also

65
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,452
a punishment

66
00:05:40,452 --> 00:05:42,184
and a wake-up call

67
00:05:42,184 --> 00:05:46,221
for letting myself slack off lately.

68
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,600
How so?

69
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,068
To be honest, even with my English score added,

70
00:05:51,068 --> 00:05:52,756
my monthly test results won't get me

71
00:05:52,756 --> 00:05:55,480
into the university I want.

72
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,686
What's more,

73
00:05:56,686 --> 00:05:58,664
in the Gaokao,

74
00:05:58,664 --> 00:06:01,600
Cao Fan won't be my only rival.

75
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:05,190
So I need to readjust my study methods

76
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:07,750
and push myself harder.

77
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,560
Do you believe I can make it?

78
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,680
Of course.

79
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,950
So certain?

80
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:14,070
Why?

81
00:06:14,070 --> 00:06:15,120
No reason.

82
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,883
I just believe in you.

83
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:21,920
In that case,

84
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,600
you can also believe

85
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,240
that I can get both of us

86
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,912
onto the honor roll.

87
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,998
I'm not like you.

88
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,510
I haven't studied for years.

89
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:34,840
I probably

90
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:37,109
won't get into college.

91
00:06:37,109 --> 00:06:39,240
Where there's a will, there's a way.

92
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,531
How will you know if you don't try?

93
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:44,519
Don't waste your time on me.

94
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:46,200
Besides, I'm going back to school

95
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,534
not to get into college.

96
00:06:47,534 --> 00:06:49,360
I know.

97
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,160
Just to get your high school diploma.

98
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:54,010
Exactly.

99
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:00,400
That's about enough. Any longer
and your feet will turn into braised trotters.

100
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,454
Lift them up.

101
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,603
Good night.

102
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,400
Morning, Xing Wu.

103
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,837
Morning, Qing Ye.

104
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,750
You look much more like a proper student.

105
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,870
Like I wasn't proper before.

106
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:33,560
Back then you were Mr. Xing.

107
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,480
Now, you're a student.

108
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,750
Which one is better?

109
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,550
- Both are good.
- You have to pick one.

110
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:40,049
Can't I pick both?

111
00:09:40,049 --> 00:09:41,520
Dream on.

112
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,804
You evolved, right?
You've become much more outgoing.

113
00:09:43,804 --> 00:09:45,080
You even crack jokes now.

114
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,720
No way. Give me a break.

115
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,240
Ever done Myers-Briggs?

116
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,468
What's that?

117
00:09:49,468 --> 00:09:51,000
Though you were an introvert,

118
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,305
you're becoming an extrovert.

119
00:09:52,305 --> 00:09:53,840
Introvert, extrovert.

120
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,101
Right now,

121
00:09:55,101 --> 00:09:56,510
I'm a high school student.

122
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:57,538
Let's go.

123
00:09:57,538 --> 00:09:59,080
Wait.

124
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,720
You're not a complete high school student yet.

125
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,516
Where's your ID badge?

126
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,225
Forgot to put it on.

127
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,981
Let me help you.

128
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,870
There.

129
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:23,150
- Is it level?
- Yes.

130
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:25,080
Perfectly level.

131
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,920
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

132
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:30,358
Nice day, isn't it?

133
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,180
What are you listening to?

134
00:10:53,459 --> 00:10:54,480
English.

135
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,254
Listening practice.

136
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,549
Listen with me?

137
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,235
I-I'm not interested.

138
00:11:33,947 --> 00:11:36,720
So? Does it sound good?

139
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,206
Yeah.

140
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:42,000
What's the name of it?

141
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,157
I Promise.

142
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,441
Quite nice.

143
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,240
Try another one.

144
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,720
Listening material?

145
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,301
No.

146
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,359
You're listening.

147
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:08,595
Whatever you say.

148
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:43,003
Oh, by the way...

149
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,129
Getting used to it?

150
00:13:43,129 --> 00:13:44,680
This uniform is so uncomfortable.

151
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,524
Qing Ye!

152
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:49,720
Look, who's this?

153
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,920
Who else could it be?

154
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:53,143
New sneakers.

155
00:13:53,143 --> 00:13:54,595
New haircut.

156
00:13:54,595 --> 00:13:56,452
Time to celebrate!

157
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:01,000
Don't step on my new sneakers!

158
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,870
- You want to lose a foot?
- Don't you know the saying?

159
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:05,030
Step on new shoes twice,
and no worries on your path.

160
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:08,142
Rub a new haircut once,
and you'll be smart and bouncy.

161
00:14:08,142 --> 00:14:11,360
See? Since he heard you're coming back,
he's even stopped stuttering.

162
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,200
Y-Y-You bet!

163
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:16,003
I'm even planning to stick around
for another year. Grade four.

164
00:14:16,003 --> 00:14:18,440
Don't say things that bad luck brings.

165
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,680
Then I'll be your all-around companion:

166
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,342
companion of study, food, and drink.

167
00:14:23,342 --> 00:14:24,840
I'll stay as long as you guys do.

168
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:27,038
Enough of such words.

169
00:14:27,038 --> 00:14:29,298
What if I already regret

170
00:14:29,298 --> 00:14:30,440
going back to school?

171
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,412
- Too late.
- Too late.

172
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:37,459
- Y-You dare run!
- Wait for me!

173
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,679
Go!

174
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,529
Frankly speaking, I do admire Xing Wu.

175
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,880
For what?

176
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:56,560
Not many in Anzi County can turn down my dad.

177
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,340
But he did.

178
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:01,920
That's just how he is.

179
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,870
He sets his mind,

180
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:06,710
and he'll do it no matter the cost.

181
00:15:06,710 --> 00:15:09,163
I wish I could be like that.

182
00:15:11,230 --> 00:15:12,750
By the way, Shu Han,

183
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:15,115
you don't have to pick me up
after school anymore.

184
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:19,052
Why? Got other plans?

185
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:24,080
I'm staying for the evening study session
to review with Qing Ye.

186
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,800
You're pretty tired after work anyway.

187
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,110
I'll just take a taxi home.

188
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:30,400
Anyway, if anything comes up,
just call me anytime.

189
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,004
Okay.

190
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,000
<i>Sorry.</i>

191
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,819
<i>I can't sign the contract.</i>

192
00:15:49,819 --> 00:15:50,870
<i>Why?</i>

193
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:52,240
<i>If it's about the salary,</i>

194
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,040
<i>I can talk to Mr. Ye again.</i>

195
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,630
<i>It's no trouble.</i>

196
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:57,160
<i>No.</i>

197
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,066
<i>It's not about the salary.</i>

198
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:01,560
<i>I've decided to go back to school.</i>

199
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,356
<i>Back to school?</i>

200
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,160
<i>Are you serious?</i>

201
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:08,030
<i>What made you change your mind all of a sudden?</i>

202
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,560
<i>To get</i>

203
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,678
<i>a high school diploma.</i>

204
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,830
<i>Oh, come on.</i>

205
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:19,212
<i>If you just wanted a diploma,
you would've made it a long time ago.</i>

206
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,120
<i>It's because of Qing Ye, right?</i>

207
00:16:28,710 --> 00:16:30,710
<i>Looks like I hit the mark.</i>

208
00:16:30,710 --> 00:16:32,510
<i>Spill it. What's going on?</i>

209
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:34,675
<i>I want to protect her as much as I can.</i>

210
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:36,750
<i>Keep her from being disturbed.</i>

211
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:39,400
<i>So she can focus on preparing for Gaokao.</i>

212
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,980
<i>Xing Wu,</i>

213
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,280
<i>you're so good to Qing Ye.</i>

214
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:46,120
<i>You're even giving up</i>

215
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:48,839
<i>this job opportunity for her?</i>

216
00:16:51,957 --> 00:16:53,110
<i>Fine.</i>

217
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:55,560
<i>But as your friend, I have to tell you,</i>

218
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,440
<i>someday, Qing Ye will leave this place.</i>

219
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,040
<i>She'll leave Zhazhating</i>

220
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,200
<i>to see father's places.</i>

221
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,960
<i>Maybe by then,
she won't even remember this place.</i>

222
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,270
<i>I know.</i>

223
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:08,070
<i>You can walk this stretch of the road with her.</i>

224
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:09,760
<i>- I know that too.
- So what?</i>

225
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,800
<i>Then what about later?</i>

226
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,614
<i>What about the future?</i>

227
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,520
<i>It doesn't matter to me</i>

228
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:21,329
<i>whether she's still here later,</i>

229
00:17:21,329 --> 00:17:22,470
<i>or whether she remembers this place or not.</i>

230
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:24,400
<i>I can only control the present,</i>

231
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,270
<i>making sure she goes through her time here</i>

232
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:28,710
<i>smoothly and safely.</i>

233
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:31,032
<i>I've always been by your side.</i>

234
00:17:32,310 --> 00:17:33,840
<i>If one day,</i>

235
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:35,710
<i>you're tired of being a student,</i>

236
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:38,244
<i>you're always welcome to come back as Mr. Xing.</i>

237
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:43,118
<i>I'm busy. You can see yourself out.
I won't walk you.</i>

238
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:55,030
[China Sports Lottery]

239
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,760
Qing Ye,

240
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:22,755
could you do me a favor?

241
00:18:22,755 --> 00:18:24,466
Go ahead.

242
00:18:25,470 --> 00:18:29,591
Could you give this to your brother, Xing Wu?

243
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:33,677
Thank you so much.

244
00:18:38,892 --> 00:18:40,000
Wu,

245
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,640
I heard that you used to be
a beast at shooting games.

246
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,190
They called you the Sniper King.

247
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,030
Could you carry us in games after school?

248
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:48,520
I used to play games, but not anymore.

249
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,230
What? Are you all about studying now?

250
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,680
No wonder you're doing so well.
Always first in physics.

251
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:57,430
- Got any tips to share?
- Yeah. Share with us!

252
00:18:57,430 --> 00:19:00,167
- I want to hear it too.
- Why crowing around?

253
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,640
Because I'm into it.

254
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:05,120
That's all.

255
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:07,600
That's so vague. Elaborate a bit?

256
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,160
Instead of asking me,

257
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,720
you'd better drill on practice problems.

258
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:12,800
We do grind problems,
but with the same practice material,

259
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:13,950
why do you always score higher?

260
00:19:13,950 --> 00:19:15,960
- Yeah!
- What kind of problems do you solve?

261
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,800
- Don't you use the Five-Three Workbook?
- Right. Are you taking private lessons?

262
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,320
- A tutoring class?
- You must be secretly studying every night.

263
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,710
- I don't want to hear excuses.
- Grinder.

264
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:25,480
Didn't expect you to be this popular

265
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,507
right after returning to school.

266
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,800
Of course.

267
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:32,120
I'm just that attractive.

268
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,120
- Indeed.
- Yeah.

269
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,839
Look, Wu just transferred into our class,

270
00:19:34,839 --> 00:19:36,360
great at games,

271
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,965
great at studies, and handsome, too.

272
00:19:38,965 --> 00:19:41,600
He is so excellent.

273
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,190
Simply excellent.

274
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:45,640
No wonder everyone admires him.

275
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,040
Speaking of it,

276
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,600
someone gave you yogurt.

277
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,880
Yogurt?

278
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,929
Who is the "someone"?

279
00:19:51,929 --> 00:19:53,430
- Break it up. Everyone, break it up.
- Let me have a look.

280
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:55,268
Go on.

281
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,120
So there's yogurt.

282
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,920
If you're not drinking it, I will.

283
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,537
Thanks.

284
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,328
Where did you get it?

285
00:20:21,328 --> 00:20:22,360
It's Xing Wu's.

286
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,510
Who told you to drink it? It wasn't for you.

287
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:26,800
Well then, was it for you?

288
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,795
I bought it. I gave it to Xing Wu.

289
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,560
Here, take it back.

290
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:37,120
Get lost.

291
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:40,514
"I bought it. I gave it to Xing Wu."

292
00:21:08,303 --> 00:21:09,983
Going for a late-night snack?

293
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,349
Not going.

294
00:21:14,030 --> 00:21:15,950
Qing Ye. Late-night snack?

295
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:17,080
Not going.

296
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,480
Have some?

297
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,340
You've already torn it apart.

298
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,190
Qing Ye.

299
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:24,506
Here.

300
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,430
I didn't find problems in English,

301
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:29,560
but found out

302
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:31,120
some new problems in math.

303
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:32,990
This question type is quite new,

304
00:21:32,990 --> 00:21:35,190
but it's still related to functions.

305
00:21:35,190 --> 00:21:36,750
Look at him, Ye Ying Jian.

306
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,470
Ever since the monthly exams ended,

307
00:21:38,470 --> 00:21:41,030
he's been sticking to Qing Ye every night.
Can't even chase him away.

308
00:21:41,030 --> 00:21:42,880
If I weren't incapable of studying,

309
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:45,648
I'd squeeze right between them, shove him out.

310
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:47,760
Don't bother me.

311
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,800
Go find Hu for a snack.

312
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,560
Hu?

313
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,840
Forget it. Let me tell you, class just ended,

314
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,320
and he's already vanished.

315
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:57,274
Before he left, he said something like

316
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:59,000
"I-I-I'm not going."

317
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:02,412
"I-I-I've got other important stuff."

318
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,165
"Be kind to your hands."

319
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,674
Smells so good.

320
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:45,222
Thank you.

321
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,880
It was supposed to be a show for four:

322
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,760
You, Qing Ye,

323
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:04,880
me, and Hu.

324
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,255
But what happened?

325
00:23:06,255 --> 00:23:07,880
I'm still the nameless one.

326
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:09,470
Like an empty-nester.

327
00:23:09,470 --> 00:23:11,685
Take your time for your cousin!

328
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:14,760
Xing Wu, I heard you know how to fix phones.

329
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,640
Mine is broken. Could you take a look?

330
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:18,446
- Mine is broken too.
- Mine too.

331
00:23:18,446 --> 00:23:20,146
- Okay.
- You're so kind.

332
00:23:20,146 --> 00:23:22,560
I'll take them back and check.
Then I'll let you know in a few days.

333
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:25,480
That would be great. Sorry for the trouble.

334
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:27,666
- You're welcome.
- Thanks.

335
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:45,480
- Volunteer.
- Volunteer.

336
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:48,360
- It's "volunteer," right?
- Your vocabulary is actually enough.

337
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:51,270
I find English lessons easy now.

338
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:54,180
I just wrote down that word at the time.

339
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:08,160
I'm heading off.

340
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,560
Bye. See you tomorrow.

341
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:11,177
Bye.

342
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,270
Had fun studying English, huh?

343
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:41,741
Had fun chatting with them, huh?

344
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:45,349
You've been busy.

345
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,510
- Not bad.
- Got to open it up and see.

346
00:24:48,510 --> 00:24:49,560
Of course I do.

347
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,950
Open each one and check carefully.

348
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:53,800
Each one.

349
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,470
So there's more than one?

350
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:58,230
Yeah, quite a few.

351
00:24:58,230 --> 00:25:00,789
Didn't expect to be this popular.

352
00:25:01,990 --> 00:25:04,080
Just enjoy it quietly.

353
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,640
I can't enjoy it alone.

354
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:08,037
It's all thanks to you. I should share the joy.

355
00:25:08,037 --> 00:25:10,144
What do you mean by that?

356
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:13,432
Treat you to a late-night snack.

357
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,200
Got a few phone repair jobs.

358
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,320
Everyone gets a cut.

359
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,259
Happy with the money.

360
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:27,708
So it's about phones?

361
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:31,480
What else did you think?

362
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,497
Nothing.

363
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:39,016
Wrong way.

364
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:41,619
This way.

365
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,670
What do you feel like eating?

366
00:25:54,670 --> 00:25:56,430
Whatever. Anything is fine.

367
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,840
I'm so full.

368
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:09,640
Next time, I'll definitely not eat this much.

369
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,000
I wonder who kept saying,

370
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:14,219
"Good. Delicious. Yummy."

371
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:19,950
- Where did this rain come from?
- Here, over here.

372
00:26:19,950 --> 00:26:22,054
Seriously, no warning at all.

373
00:26:22,054 --> 00:26:24,320
It just pours whenever it wants.

374
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:25,400
Probably a passing shower.

375
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,430
Comes fast, goes fast.

376
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:29,600
Shoot, no umbrella.

377
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:31,430
Wait here. I'll go back and get one.

378
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:33,149
Forget it. It's only a few steps.

379
00:26:33,149 --> 00:26:34,430
Let's run back together.

380
00:26:34,430 --> 00:26:35,560
Are you kidding me?

381
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:38,840
It's not like
we haven't been caught in the rain before.

382
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:41,470
Wait a second. I'm getting my jacket out.

383
00:26:41,470 --> 00:26:42,750
Scoot in.

384
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:44,230
Come here.

385
00:26:44,230 --> 00:26:45,823
Come on.

386
00:26:46,886 --> 00:26:49,160
- Got a good grip?
- Got it.

387
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,873
You sure?

388
00:26:50,873 --> 00:26:52,579
Ready?

389
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:54,928
Three.

390
00:26:54,928 --> 00:26:57,166
- Two. One.
- Two. One.

391
00:27:40,190 --> 00:27:41,744
Oh my!

392
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,413
Don't move.

393
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,360
Go inside. Don't catch a cold.

394
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:55,878
Okay.

395
00:29:32,190 --> 00:29:34,230
<i>What's Xing Wu</i>

396
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:36,228
<i>doing now?</i>

397
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:40,560
<i>What are you thinking about, Qing Ye?</i>

398
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:42,593
<i>You should go to sleep.</i>

399
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:49,680
Grandma.

400
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:51,920
You're still up?

401
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,301
Ye.

402
00:29:53,301 --> 00:29:55,589
Come in.

403
00:29:58,280 --> 00:30:00,710
Aren't you awake too?

404
00:30:00,710 --> 00:30:05,230
I want to wind up this yarn before I sleep.

405
00:30:05,230 --> 00:30:06,520
Let me help you.

406
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:07,600
Good.

407
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,349
Like this, right?

408
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,686
- Yes.
- Like this.

409
00:30:11,686 --> 00:30:13,560
Pull it straight.

410
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:16,218
- Okay.
- Good.

411
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:21,320
You're up so late.

412
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:24,320
What's wrong? Something on your mind?

413
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,024
No.

414
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:28,577
Not really?

415
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:31,600
Alright,

416
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,218
maybe a little.

417
00:30:33,950 --> 00:30:35,975
Tell me about it.

418
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,000
It's just that

419
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,120
lately I feel

420
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:45,470
all mixed up inside.

421
00:30:45,470 --> 00:30:47,980
I keep thinking about one thing,

422
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,880
trying to

423
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:53,203
sort it out.

424
00:30:53,203 --> 00:30:54,840
There's this person

425
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:56,120
who makes your emotions

426
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,160
go up and down wildly.

427
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:00,692
Grandma, do you know that feeling?

428
00:31:01,270 --> 00:31:02,990
Well, that means,

429
00:31:02,990 --> 00:31:04,560
when he's happy,

430
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:05,880
you're happy.

431
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:08,423
And when he's unhappy, you get worried.

432
00:31:08,423 --> 00:31:11,360
- Is that how it feels?
- Yes!

433
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:12,920
Grandma, I feel like

434
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,160
my emotions

435
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,160
have become unstable.

436
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,840
I know this isn't right,

437
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:21,650
but I just can't figure out what's going on.

438
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,840
You know,

439
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:26,840
if you try to make everything
in life crystal clear,

440
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:29,360
then it would be quite boring.

441
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,200
In one's life,

442
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:33,030
if everything is perfectly right,

443
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:35,037
then it's all wrong.

444
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:37,360
I think you're

445
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:38,430
doing just fine.

446
00:31:38,430 --> 00:31:39,800
It's no big deal.

447
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,324
It's okay. Don't worry.

448
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:45,430
Grandma,

449
00:31:45,430 --> 00:31:48,270
you are a philosopher indeed.

450
00:31:48,270 --> 00:31:50,141
A philosopher?

451
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,102
What philosopher?

452
00:31:52,102 --> 00:31:54,030
It's a title.

453
00:31:54,030 --> 00:31:57,197
It means you're perceptive and wise.

454
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:00,387
Who gave me that title?

455
00:32:01,853 --> 00:32:04,230
Your grandson, Xing Wu.

456
00:32:04,230 --> 00:32:06,865
Oh, he's talking nonsense.

457
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:25,553
Fang!

458
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:28,066
Xing Wu!

459
00:33:29,470 --> 00:33:32,190
- Help! Fang!
- Xi Xi? What's wrong?

460
00:33:32,190 --> 00:33:34,030
Please help me!

461
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:35,600
I need your help!

462
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:38,166
- What happened?
- Hu is missing!

463
00:33:38,166 --> 00:33:39,400
Missing?

464
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:41,030
When did you find out?

465
00:33:41,030 --> 00:33:42,200
Just now!

466
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:45,294
Don't panic. Come inside. Come in.

467
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:47,640
Take your time.

468
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:50,030
Tell us about it.

469
00:33:50,030 --> 00:33:52,920
Yesterday, I scolded him a bit,

470
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,360
and then he got upset.

471
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:55,600
- What's up?
- Wu.

472
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,990
- What's up?
- Has Hu contacted you?

473
00:33:57,990 --> 00:33:59,240
No.

474
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:01,680
That's it. He must have run away from home.

475
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:04,120
Auntie, don't panic. Take your time.
What's going on exactly?

476
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,972
I scolded him a bit yesterday.

477
00:34:05,972 --> 00:34:07,920
He got upset and talked back,

478
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:10,240
and then we ended up arguing.

479
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:12,430
Hu doesn't seem like the type to argue.

480
00:34:12,430 --> 00:34:14,630
I know, yesterday not only did we argue,

481
00:34:14,630 --> 00:34:16,800
he even slammed the door and left.

482
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:19,704
I said to him,
"Fine. Don't you dare come back!"

483
00:34:19,704 --> 00:34:22,163
That was just angry talk.

484
00:34:22,163 --> 00:34:23,920
When I get mad at Wu,

485
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:26,430
I say way worse things.

486
00:34:26,430 --> 00:34:29,360
I thought he just went out to clear his head.

487
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,040
But this morning I checked:

488
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:33,880
he wasn't in his room.
The blanket was still folded.

489
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:36,030
I realized he never came home last night.

490
00:34:36,030 --> 00:34:38,080
[Hu]
Did you call him? Try to reach him?

491
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,633
Well...

492
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,760
His phone is with me.

493
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:49,550
To avoid online romance, I took his phone.

494
00:34:49,550 --> 00:34:51,240
Online romance?

495
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:54,110
No way. He is such an honest and simple kid.

496
00:34:54,110 --> 00:34:56,280
How could he? Don't overthink it.

497
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:59,461
You have no idea
how mature kids these days could be.

498
00:35:00,653 --> 00:35:02,030
Wu,

499
00:35:02,030 --> 00:35:03,720
unlock his phone for me.

500
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,840
Let me check.

501
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,590
Auntie, I can't.

502
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:09,665
I can't unlock it.

503
00:35:11,420 --> 00:35:12,630
Then what should we do?

504
00:35:12,630 --> 00:35:14,030
Where to look for him?

505
00:35:14,030 --> 00:35:16,080
I'll go with you to the police station.

506
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,720
Okay.

507
00:35:17,720 --> 00:35:20,160
Wu. If he contacts you, let me know right away.

508
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,727
- Sure. No problem.
- Let's go.

509
00:35:21,727 --> 00:35:24,030
- You two watch the shop.
- Yes.

510
00:35:24,030 --> 00:35:25,755
Take your time.

511
00:35:29,583 --> 00:35:31,110
Why didn't you just unlock it?

512
00:35:31,110 --> 00:35:33,200
That would be a total betrayal.

513
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:34,920
Besides, that's an invasion of privacy.

514
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:37,100
But what if he runs into danger?

515
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:38,470
It won't come to that.

516
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:39,920
I know him.

517
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:42,680
He probably has a hidden problem.

518
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:45,030
None of you has seen him?

519
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:46,200
All right.

520
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:47,280
I got it.

521
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:50,470
If you do see him, call me anytime.

522
00:35:50,470 --> 00:35:52,721
Okay.

523
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:00,120
I asked a few friends.

524
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,800
None of them has seen Hu.

525
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,720
Internet cafes, arcades,

526
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:05,950
Even in hotels, nobody's seen him.

527
00:36:05,950 --> 00:36:07,590
I also asked our classmates.

528
00:36:07,590 --> 00:36:10,590
No one has any news of him.

529
00:36:10,590 --> 00:36:12,120
Lately,

530
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:14,360
Hu has indeed been acting a bit off.

531
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:16,840
Yeah, something's off.

532
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,070
But in what way?

533
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:21,590
In so many ways.

534
00:36:21,590 --> 00:36:24,430
Ever since the start of this semester,

535
00:36:24,430 --> 00:36:25,800
I've felt something was up.

536
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:28,000
He often wouldn't walk home with me
after school.

537
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,440
Whenever he's free, he holds his phone
and giggle like an idiot.

538
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:32,240
One time, I even caught him
chatting with someone at an internet cafe.

539
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,040
Why did you show up all of a sudden?

540
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:36,201
My mom went to the police station with them.

541
00:36:36,201 --> 00:36:37,800
I haven't eaten. Thought I'd come for a meal.

542
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:40,320
- Are you full?
- Yes.

543
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,800
- Thanks.
- Wait.

544
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:43,800
I was saving it for later!

545
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,000
Don't worry.

546
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:47,360
Men destined for greatness
don't sweat the small stuff.

547
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,760
I'm not like my mom.

548
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:50,960
She makes a big deal out of everything
and even went to the police.

549
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,000
Oh, come on,

550
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,150
Hu isn't that fragile.

551
00:36:54,150 --> 00:36:55,749
I reckon he's just hiding somewhere

552
00:36:55,749 --> 00:36:58,800
to get some peace and quiet.

553
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,240
So, according to you, once he clears his head,

554
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:03,320
he might give us a call, right?

555
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:05,486
You never know.

556
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:12,360
- Hello?
<i>- Wu.</i>

557
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:14,221
Hu!

558
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:18,990
Hu, where are you?

559
00:37:18,990 --> 00:37:20,510
<i>I'm in Changdao.</i>

560
00:37:20,510 --> 00:37:22,150
Changdao?

561
00:37:22,150 --> 00:37:24,680
What are you doing there?

562
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,280
<i>It's a long story.</i>

563
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:29,590
Dude, you left without your phone,
and didn't come home last night.

564
00:37:29,590 --> 00:37:31,030
Your mom is going crazy looking for you.

565
00:37:31,030 --> 00:37:33,507
Don't tell her I'm here.

566
00:37:33,507 --> 00:37:34,680
<i>Please don't.</i>

567
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,108
She went to the police.

568
00:37:36,108 --> 00:37:38,720
By now, she's probably at the station.

569
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:39,760
Wu,

570
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:42,280
why didn't you stop her?

571
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,280
<i>It's not that I didn't try.
She wouldn't be stopped.</i>

572
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,550
<i>Hu,</i>

573
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:46,800
we can keep your secret,

574
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:48,680
but you have to let your mom know
that you're safe.

575
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:51,040
She's about to die of worry.

576
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:54,000
Okay, I'll tell her.

577
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,320
<i>When are you coming back?</i>

578
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:58,118
Hard to say.

579
00:37:58,118 --> 00:38:00,468
Things are pretty complicated here.

580
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:04,340
Bro, I'm not done yet.

581
00:38:04,340 --> 00:38:05,924
Hello?

582
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:09,920
Young man. I'm in a hurry to deliver goods.

583
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:13,110
O-O-One more minute. Just one minute.

584
00:38:13,110 --> 00:38:16,199
- Alright. Make it quick.
- Thank you.

585
00:38:21,463 --> 00:38:23,920
Mom. It's me.

586
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:26,430
Get it boxed up and shipped out.

587
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:28,400
You have to take a boat

588
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,268
to get to Changdao.

589
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:32,360
Are you going for him?

590
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:33,613
Then I'll go with you.

591
00:38:33,613 --> 00:38:34,840
The ferry runs only three trips a day.

592
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:37,330
We might not make the morning one.

593
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:41,232
Tell me a family here without a boat.

594
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:44,195
Fuzz.

595
00:38:44,195 --> 00:38:45,742
Here you are.

596
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,744
Have some water.

597
00:38:54,510 --> 00:38:55,680
I have

598
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:57,880
a wild guess.

599
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,984
- What?
- Look.

600
00:39:00,950 --> 00:39:02,550
[There's something I wish for]
This is Shi Min's Moments Post.

601
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:03,800
This photo

602
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:06,240
is identical to Hu's Moments cover.

603
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:08,510
So it was Shi Min all along.

604
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,280
I'm not sure.

605
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,880
But Shi Min told me before

606
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:13,030
that she boards at school

607
00:39:13,030 --> 00:39:15,240
because commuting is too much trouble.

608
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:16,920
She has to transfer three times.

609
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,760
Her home is on Changdao.

610
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,760
Look at you, Sherlock Holmes.

611
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:23,400
Well, girls have a certain intuition

612
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:24,880
for this kind of thing.

613
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:26,680
Who's good with who and who's not,

614
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,320
we can tell right away.

615
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:30,200
Then should you call Shi Min?

616
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:32,000
Right, I'll call her now.

617
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,075
[Shi Min]

618
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,630
<i>Hello, Qing Ye.</i>

619
00:39:39,630 --> 00:39:40,880
Hello, Shi Min.

620
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:42,360
Have you been in touch with Hu?

621
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:45,563
<i>He's with me right now.</i>

622
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:50,200
Send us your location right away.

623
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:53,330
His mom is freaking out.
She's already gone to the police.

624
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,194
Let's set off.

625
00:39:55,194 --> 00:39:56,567
How?

626
00:40:00,463 --> 00:40:01,510
You drive.

627
00:40:01,510 --> 00:40:03,240
Don't judge a book by its cover.

628
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:06,320
Hard to find a Zhazhating resident
who doesn't know how to drive a boat.

629
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,510
[PRC Yacht Driver's License]

630
00:40:08,510 --> 00:40:09,630
Then let's head out.

631
00:40:09,630 --> 00:40:11,472
Let's go, Captain.

632
00:40:18,690 --> 00:40:20,030
Hold on tight.

633
00:40:20,030 --> 00:40:21,815
Let's go.

634
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:39,760
Thank you. We'll cancel it.

635
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:41,110
Hurry, hurry.

636
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,470
What's wrong? Hurry up.

637
00:40:42,470 --> 00:40:43,680
Slow down.

638
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,200
Go to Changdao. He's there.

639
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,600
How did you know he was in Changdao?

640
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:49,920
I overheard someone on the phone with Hu

641
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:52,400
mentioned farms and oysters.

642
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:55,150
Around here, only Changdao has oyster farms.

643
00:40:55,150 --> 00:40:57,680
That's true. But Changdao is huge.

644
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,160
Are we going to search door-to-door?

645
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:02,150
Fine, door-to-door it is.

646
00:41:02,150 --> 00:41:05,080
I'm to blame.
I shouldn't have yelled at him yesterday.

647
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:07,760
Boys are tough. So what if you yelled?

648
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:08,800
I...

649
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:11,630
I didn't just scold him, I hit him too.

650
00:41:11,630 --> 00:41:13,983
You laid hands on him?

651
00:41:13,983 --> 00:41:15,880
I just slapped his back,

652
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:18,550
poked his head, and pulled his ear.

653
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:22,070
That's nothing.
That's not even considered hitting.

654
00:41:22,070 --> 00:41:23,800
I also said,

655
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:25,680
"Look at you, you can't even speak clearly.

656
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,030
What girl would ever like you?

657
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:29,934
If you don't study hard,
what's going to become of you?"

658
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,800
That was really hurtful, right?

659
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:37,505
- Yes.
- Yes.

660
00:41:38,326 --> 00:41:40,200
He wouldn't do something stupid

661
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:42,280
like jump into the sea, would he?

662
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,590
Don't say that. Yu Fen,

663
00:41:44,590 --> 00:41:47,360
does your husband go out to Changdao often?

664
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:49,760
Yes. Let's go back to Zhazhating now.

665
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:52,800
Head to the dock,
and have him take us there by boat.

666
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:53,950
Hurry, let's go.

667
00:41:53,950 --> 00:41:56,080
- Take care!
- Hurry!

668
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,892
Oh my god.

669
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:04,110
Wait, no. Where's our boat?

670
00:42:04,110 --> 00:42:06,470
Yeah, where is it?

671
00:42:06,470 --> 00:42:07,990
Oh no. Crap.

672
00:42:07,990 --> 00:42:09,240
The key is gone too.

673
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:10,450
Seriously, who was it?

674
00:42:10,450 --> 00:42:12,480
Who took our boat?

675
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:14,950
I don't even need to think twice.

676
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:16,996
Our little rascal took it.

677
00:42:16,996 --> 00:42:19,920
Fuzz! I'm going to knock you into next week!

678
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,000
Come on.

679
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:23,150
- Catch a ferry at the dock.
- Go, go, go.

680
00:42:23,150 --> 00:42:25,966
Honey, go ahead with your work. We're leaving.

681
00:42:57,430 --> 00:42:59,482
It's just up ahead.

682
00:43:12,990 --> 00:43:14,933
It's vast out here.

683
00:43:17,510 --> 00:43:19,568
Careful, cousin.

684
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,470
- Massive.
- Excuse me, coming through.

685
00:43:32,470 --> 00:43:35,800
Everyone's bundled up.
How are we supposed to find him?

686
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:36,920
I've asked around.

687
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:39,824
This is the Shi family's seafood farm.

